  "texts": [
    "In response, the LLM is highly likely to reply a PLAY or RECORD message, as indicated by the study results in Section III-C.",
    "These messages lead the server to transition to a different state, overcoming the coverage plateau.",
    "D. ImplementationWe implemented this LLM-guided protocol fuzzing (cf.",
    "Algorithm 1) into AFLNET [36], called CHATAFL, to test protocols written in C/C++.",
    "AFLNET is one of the most popular mutation-based open-source protocol fuzzers 6."
